This paper is about a machine learning algorithm for positive unlabeled (PU) learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper proposes a novel scalable PU learning algorithm that is theoretically proven to provide the optimal solution, while showing superior computational and memory performance. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
